      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification using manufactured solutions must be demonstrated for all governing equations including the hemolysis transport equation.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests confirm second-order spatial convergence for Navier-Stokes; the scalar hemolysis transport equation was verified only to first order due to boundary treatment. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI must be computed on three systematically refined meshes; GCI must be below 5% for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study performed; GCI for velocity fields is 3.2%. GCI for hemolysis index QoI is 8.7%, exceeding the 5% threshold. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
